Por qu este Coloquio?

La IA generativa est impactando la docencia, la evaluacin, la tutora, la investigacin y la gestin universitaria. Este Coloquio ofrece un espacio de debate y construccin de rutas de accin institucional para sostener la calidad, la equidad y la pertinencia en educacin superior.

  • Analizar crticamente el impacto de la IAG en la calidad, la equidad y la pertinencia.
  • Compartir experiencias innovadoras de integracin de IAG en docencia y gestin acadmica.
  • Disear rutas de accin para un liderazgo flexible, colaborativo y basado en evidencia.

1st International Colloquium
Academic Leadership in the Era of Generative Artificial Intelligence

A high-level international event for leaders, faculty and researchers focused on strategic, ethical and evidence-based adoption of Generative AI in higher education.

Dates: Pre-events July 2021, 2026 Main event July 2224, 2026 6 hours/day Certificate issued by Centurion International University (USA).
Register as attendee Submit abstract (Presenter) View fees

Why this Colloquium?

Generative AI is reshaping teaching, assessment, tutoring, research and academic management. This Colloquium provides a strategic space to discuss impacts on quality, equity and relevanceand to build actionable institutional pathways.

  • Critically analyze GenAIs impact on quality, equity and relevance in higher education.
  • Share innovative experiences integrating GenAI into teaching and academic management.
  • Design concrete action routes for flexible, collaborative and evidence-based leadership.

Organizers

Centurion International University (Florida, USA)

Committed to educational innovation, research and global leadership development.

ALSIE S.R.L. University Agency

International academic cooperation, research, and postgraduate program development.

Thematic tracks

A. Leadership & strategic transformation

Governance, planning and decision-making with GenAI.

B. Pedagogical innovation

GenAI-assisted teaching: course design, assessment and tutoring.

C. Research & knowledge production

Workflows, integrity and quality in GenAI-enabled scholarship.

D. Ethics, humanism & leadership

Bias, transparency and institutional responsibility.

E. GenAI competencies

Capability development for faculty and students.

F. Curriculum innovation

New models and curriculum redesign.
